Prince Harry and Meghan Markle have been facing increasing criticism, particularly since their bombshell interview with Oprah Winfrey last year. Speaking on the latest episode of Royally Us, hosts Christina Garibaldi and Christine Ross discussed the Duke and Duchess of Sussexes' negative attention and how the couple have been warned that the "negative stories" are spoken about more than the good. Ms Garibaldi said: "Getting all this bad press, it's, kind of, hard to turn a blind eye to it." Ms Ross added: "We talk, much more, about these negative stories about Meghan and Harry than we do about anything positive that they're doing. "These stories really detract from the work that they're trying to get done." Ms Garibaldi said: "Tom Bower did, in that interview he did, say some some good things about her in the book. READ MORE: Queen shares hilarious reaction to Kate and Prince William's renovated kitchen "[He said] she is a hard worker, she is very diligent and assertive and things like that. "So there are some positives in the story, but, of course, everyone loves to focus on [the negative]." Ms Ross added: "They're trying to do important things but these really nasty stories keep coming out of the woodwork. "I'm sure it's very distracting from the work that they are trying to get done." READ MORE: Royal Family LIVE: Queen SNUBS Harry in shock speech as monarch heaps praise on William Speaking of the bad press, Ms Garibaldi said: "It's not a good look for the Sussexes, it really isn't. "For one couple to have so much bad press, it's not, it's not good. "There's a lot of bad stories out there." DON'T MISS In January 2020, Meghan and Harry announced that they were to step down as senior working royals. The couple completed their final royal engagement in March 2020, just before the Covid pandemic took hold. Since their exit, the couple have settled in California with their two young children, Archie and Lilibet. READ NEXT: